entum carried through the first half of July, culminating in Tuesday's high of 219.62 \u2014 the strongest print in the 30-session window. Wednesday's session pulled back modestly but held above 218.68, and today's daily candle is shaping up as a narrow-range inside bar, suggesting the market is digesting rather than reversing. The broader sequence of higher lows since late June remains intact, and the desk's bias stays bullish while that structure holds.\n\nThe zone architecture beneath current price is well-defined. The 215.57 prior reaction zone \u2014 which attracted three distinct daily touches in late June and early July \u2014 now sits roughly 280 pips below spot and represents the first meaningful structural reference should the pullback extend. Below that, 214.54 has four recorded touches and marks the area where buyers reasserted control most convincingly through the June consolidation. Deeper still, the 213.57 and 213.34 clusters served as the base of the entire recovery and would only come into view on a significant deterioration of sentiment. None of these levels are under immediate threat given the current pace of the retreat, but they frame the landscape clearly.\n\nOn the H1 chart, the picture is one of orderly drift lower from the 219.40 area printed in the early hours of Thursday morning. Each hourly bar since around 02:00 has been relatively compressed, with sellers making incremental progress but finding no real momentum. The 218.27\u2013218.30 area has so far contained the downside on an intraday basis, and the absence of any sharp rejection candle from the bulls suggests this is consolidation rather than distribution. A recovery back through the 218.90\u2013219.00 area on the hourly would reinforce the view that Tuesday's high is merely being digested ahead of a further attempt higher.\n\nToday's calendar is empty of scheduled data releases, which means price action is likely to remain technically driven through the remainder of the session. Thin news flow can occasionally amplify moves if risk sentiment shifts abruptly \u2014 particularly for a yen cross \u2014 but absent a macro catalyst, the expectation is for range-bound conditions to persist into the close.\n\nThe read changes materially if price breaks and closes on the daily chart beneath the 215.57 prior reaction zone. That would fracture the sequence of higher lows and call the recovery narrative into question. A sustained move back into the 213.30\u2013213.60 cluster would represent a full structural unwind of the recent advance and would shift the desk's assessment to neutral at minimum.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}